ZH: 我的姓是王。
EN: My last name is Wang.

ZH: 他的姓氏是张。
EN: His surname is Zhang.

ZH: 你的姓什么？
EN: What is your family name?

ZH: 她的姓字很少见。
EN: Her last name is quite uncommon.

ZH: 我们合作的这位同事姓李。
EN: Our colleague we are cooperating with is surnamed Li.

ZH: 常姓是中国一个常见的姓氏。
EN: Chang is a common surname in China.

ZH: 她的姓字有三个字。
EN: Her last name has three characters.

ZH: 很多亚裔美国人的姓氏也是英文名。
EN: Many Asian Americans also have English surnames.

ZH: 爷爷的姓字是陈。
EN: Grandpa's last name is Chen.

ZH: 我的同学们有很多不同的姓氏。
EN: My classmates have various surnames.

ZH: 姓氏代表着家族的血统。
EN: A surname represents the bloodline of a family.

ZH: 华人江南姓氏多。
EN: There are many surnames of Chinese people in Jiangnan.

ZH: 他的姓氏在中国很普遍。
EN: His surname is very common in China.

ZH: 她的姓是这个城市的名字。
EN: Her last name is the name of this city.

ZH: 他和我同姓。
EN: He shares the same surname as me.

ZH: 孩子的姓要跟爸爸还是妈妈？
EN: Should the child's surname follow the father or the mother?

ZH: 她的家族姓字传承几百年。
EN: Her family surname has been passed down for hundreds of years.

ZH: 中国有很多姓氏的起源故事。
EN: There are many origin stories of surnames in China.

ZH: 我的姓在这个国家很独特。
EN: My last name is very unique in this country.

ZH: 她和我妈的姓不一样。
EN: Her surname is different from my mom's.
